casebody.data:
MASON COUNTY AUTOMOBILE DEALERS ASSOCIATION v. HANSEN.

This ease is controlled by Cadillac Auto Dealers v. DeClerk, ante, 20.

Submitted June 15, 1955. (Docket No. 51, Calendar No. 46,520.) Decided October 11, 1955. Eugene Christman, for plaintiff. Thomas M. Kavanagh, Attorney General, Edmund E. Shepherd, Solicitor General, and Maurice M. Moule, Assistant Attorney General, for defendants. Reid, J.

This case is governed by our decision in the case of Cadillac Auto Dealers v. DeClerk, anter 20.

In the instant case, the trial judge appropriately denied defendants’ motion to dismiss. The order appealed from is affirmed and the case is remanded to the trial court for further proceedings. No costs, a *507public question concerning , the statutes being involved.

Carr, C. J., and Butzel, Smith, Sharpe, Boyles, and Dethmees, JJ., concurred. Kelly, J., did not sit.
